From ad15bfc0191549c8906e7d8b0a9618ea6db2b9db Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: konard <drakonard@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 1 Jul 2026 14:20:20 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 03/44] feat(seed): add grammatical_number facet kind +
 singular/plural meanings
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Issue #538: a word form can now pin which grammatical number it
lexicalises via a `grammatical_number singular|plural` facet, so the
system records whether помидор is singular and помидоры plural of the
same meaning instead of guessing from spelling.

- meanings.rs: parse `grammatical_number` as a facet kind; add
  WordForm::part_of_speech(), grammatical_number(), denotations()
  accessors so composition is read from data, not a hardcoded table.
- meanings-lexical-meta.lino: define grammatical_number (Q104083),
  singular (Q110786), plural (Q146786) meanings with en/ru/hi/zh parity.
- ground-meanings.rs: record the three verified Wikidata anchors.
- cache: check in Q104083 entity snapshot (json + lossless lino).
