From 4a57c7d391ac952183bb43f90920ad91d8f37b0e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: konard <drakonard@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 1 Jul 2026 14:26:36 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 04/44] feat(seed): ground tomato forms with singular/plural
 detail (issue #538)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Enrich the tomato meaning so every surface carries its grammatical
number, part of speech, and Wikidata grounding, closing the помидор/томат
asymmetry the issue calls out:

- English: add the plural surface "tomatoes" (L7993-F2) alongside
  singular "tomato"; tag both with part_of_speech noun + grammatical_number.
- Russian: помидор/помидоры are singular/plural of one lexeme (L3526);
  томат/томаты are singular/plural of another (L170542) — the missing
  plural томаты is now present. Each is a grounded per-form surface.
- Hindi/Chinese surfaces tagged part_of_speech noun.
- помидор stays the first Russian surface (translation ordering).

denotation -> tomato is auto-attached per surface, so every word also
points back at the meaning it expresses (bidirectional reference).
