From 8a9d416509f5b23b76a2c7be9db06b288409db29 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: konard <drakonard@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 1 Jul 2026 16:00:24 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 14/44] feat(seed): drive Agent CLI to enrich the potato
 meaning via a different request (#538)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Prove the meaning-detail recipe is general, not tomato-hardcoded: a
*differently worded* natural-language request drives the same in-repo
Agent CLI to enrich the potato meaning — recovering the missing English
plural surface `potatoes` (form L3784-F2), pinning every surface's part
of speech and grammatical number, keeping it grounded in Wikidata
(Q10998 / L3784). The seed potato block is now byte-for-byte what the
recipe writes, enforced by a test, and the Agent CLI session is
committed as agent-cli-session-potato.json.

Adds tests: concept routing (two requests -> two concepts), byte-for-byte
seed parity, end-to-end driver run, and session freshness.
