Rewrite src/agentic_coding/meaning_detail.rs so the meaning-detail recipe
derives every enriched surface from real, checked-in Wikidata lexeme JSON
(include_str! of data/cache/wikidata/lexeme/{L7993,L3526,L170542,L3784}.json)
parsed by a general serde_json algorithm — no hardcoded answer strings.

- Remove CANONICAL_TOMATO_LEXEMES / CANONICAL_POTATO_LEXEMES answer tables,
  parse_lexemes, tomato-specific wrappers, and per-concept SEARCH_QUERY/
  SOURCE_URL/KB_PATH consts.
- Add a concept registry (Concept + SourceRef/ExtraRef) so tomato and potato
  are two data entries, not two code paths; corpus/planner drive both.
- Selection is lemma-anchored + case-key-matched: pick the singular form whose
  text equals the lemma, then the plural whose non-number grammatical features
  match — general for any case paradigm, and references no hardcoded case id
  (drops the ungrounded Q131105 dependency).
- Reproduces all four seed blocks byte-for-byte; session JSONs regenerated so
  web_fetch now returns real Wikidata JSON.
- Tests updated to assert the real JSON (L170542-F7 томаты, Q146786, etc.).

Full unit suite green (1284 passed), clippy clean, fmt clean, file within
the 1000-line guard (747).
