From ccce0ea8c5ee4f295ef59a8ae0d2de8a0b80203b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: konard <drakonard@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 2 Jul 2026 00:26:27 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 29/44] feat(agentic): admit any agent-CLI toolset via
 capability-class permissions (#538)

Bridge the Formal AI server to real agent CLIs whose toolsets carry
CLI-specific names. Classify every advertised tool through one shared
tool_capability() and gate on the capability *class*
(tool:capability:{search,fetch,write,run}) rather than an ever-growing
per-name allowlist. The agent_mode opt-in stays the real guard.

- planner: expose Capability + tool_capability; rule out lookalikes
  (todowrite/codesearch/edit/patch) so an alphabetically sorted tool
  list can never mis-pick; emit path/filePath/file_path write aliases so
  the same plan drives any CLI.
- associative_package: grant the four capability classes to the
  agentic-coding package.
- protocol_policy: replace first_tool_permission_denial with
  agentic_tool_permission_denial that gates by class through the same
  classifier the planner uses (dedup).
