The maintainer's requirements around #538 include: real logs of the Agent
CLI ↔ Formal AI round-trip (not synthesised), E2E tests in CI, a test per
requirement plus a whole-task test, hardcoded cases only in tests, small
atomic commits, and CONTRIBUTING.md containing every rule. This commit
lands the documentation half.

- docs/case-studies/issue-538/agent-cli-e2e-run.log — real captured
  console output of `experiments/agent_cli_e2e/run_agent_cli.sh`: server
  boot, the 5 /v1/chat/completions POSTs (search → fetch → write →
  bash-verify → Final), planner outcomes per round, the file listing,
  and the E2E OK assertion. Sized to the useful signal, not the
  100kB+ request bodies.
- docs/case-studies/issue-538/README.md — new subsection linking to the
  captured log with a per-round outcome table, and reproduction snippet
  (`bun add -g @link-assistant/agent` → run script).
- CONTRIBUTING.md — four new standing rules (6-9) covering the real E2E
  test requirement, hardcoded-only-in-tests policy, real-log evidence
  requirement, and small-atomic-commits requirement.
- .gitignore — un-ignore `docs/case-studies/**/*.log` so the case-study
  evidence file survives the general `*.log` ignore (with a comment
  pointing at CONTRIBUTING rule 8 so future contributors know why).
