Make the real Agent-CLI ↔ formal-ai round-trip cover every recipe axis of
issue #538, not just the tomato answer, and record both maintainer-cited
failed-reasoning logs so we never re-derive the "ship a core, defer the rest"
refusal.

- .github/workflows/release.yml: the test-agent-cli-e2e job now runs three live
  steps — tomato (search→fetch→write→verify→final), potato (differently worded,
  same recipe, proves generality), and generated diagrams (non-lexeme, no web
  step, MIN_POSTS=3). Each boots formal-ai serve and drives the real
  @link-assistant/agent CLI over the OpenAI-compatible endpoint.
- experiments/agent_cli_e2e/run_agent_cli.sh: add configurable MIN_POSTS so the
  same harness validates a no-web recipe (3 rounds) as well as the web recipes
  (5 rounds).
- docs/case-studies/issue-538/refusal-anti-pattern.md: incorporate the second
  cited gist (727ebf9) alongside the first (95b1e919) — two independent solver
  runs that reached the identical "honest scope / tracked follow-ups" refusal —
  and contrast with the correct run that drove the real CLI live.
- docs/case-studies/issue-538/agent-cli-e2e-run.log: refresh with today's live
  three-recipe capture (tomato 5 rounds, potato 5 rounds, diagram 3 rounds, all
  rc=0), so the case study carries real Agent-CLI-over-Formal-AI logs.
